==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Manilla
<hw>Ma*nil"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>manilla</ets>; cf. It. <ets>maniglio</ets>, <ets>maniglia</ets>; F.
<ets>manille</ets>; Pg. <ets>manilha</ets>; all fr. L. <ets>manus</ets>
hand, and formed after the analogy of L. <ets>monile</ets>, pl.
<ets>monilia</ets>, necklace: cf. F. <ets>manille</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A ring worn upon the arm or leg as an ornament,
especially among the tribes of Africa.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A piece of copper of the shape of a horseshoe, used
as money by certain tribes of the west coast of Africa.</def>
<rj><au>Simmonds.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Manilla</ent>⟦br⟧

